iven the very low likelihood of such an event</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and the high premiums, DfT’s view is that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">it </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">would be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> unreasonable for the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Islands</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to purchase</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> insurance. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DfT</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are therefore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">exploring </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">option of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">accepting responsibility for these costs in the unlikely event of an accident occurring within the territorial waters </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">an </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Overseas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Territor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">y</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Crown Dependenc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">y</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:3pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; fon